paragraphs.text:
run(sql="
select * from(
    select distinct b.productName, b.pogId, count(distinct a.subOrderId) as orders, row_number() over(order by COUNT(DISTINCT a.subOrderId) DESC) as rn 
    from `temp.attributed_Orders` a left join `all(agCmDump)` b 
    on a.subOrderId=b.subOrderId 
    where a.Channel LIKE 'FB%' 
    and DATEDIFF(CURRENT_DATE(),a.orderDate)<6
    group by b.productName, b.pogId
    order by orders desc)
where rn<2001
",1000)

paragraphs.text:
run(sql="
select * from(
    select distinct b.productName, b.pogId, count(distinct a.subOrderId) as orders, row_number() over(order by COUNT(DISTINCT a.subOrderId) DESC) as rn 
    from `temp.attributed_Orders` a left join `all(agCmDump)` b 
    on a.subOrderId=b.subOrderId 
    where a.Channel LIKE 'FB%' 
    and a.orderDate>'2023-02-18' AND a.orderDate<'2023-02-24'
    group by b.productName, b.pogId
    order by orders desc)
where rn<24001
",1000)

paragraphs.title: Sale_Days
paragraphs.text:
run(sql="
with cte as(
    select a.pogId, b.subOrderId 
    from `temp.SaleDays` a
    left join `all(agCmDump)` b
    on a.pogId = b.pogId
    where TO_DATE(FROM_UNIXTIME(b.orderDate/1000)) in ('2023-01-19','2023-01-20','2023-01-21','2023-01-22','2023-01-25','2023-01-26','2023-02-02','2023-02-03','2023-02-04','2023-02-05') 
)

select cte.pogId, sum(b.nm)/count(distinct cte.subOrderId) as NMBO 
from cte left join `all(unitEconomicsBaseTable)` b
on cte.subOrderId = b.subOrderId
group by cte.pogId
",1000)
